And yes, I love myself. 
Just the way I am. 
With all my flaws and my imperfections. 
It was a hard process, I have to be honest with you. I had to deal with eating disorder in the past and believe me, I‚Äôm still afraid of that monster. Because that‚Äôs what it is: 
A REAL MONSTER. 
I have never shared something so personal on here, but I‚Äôm ready to tell you parts of my story that you still don‚Äôt know.

I just have one little tip for you: 
DO NOT FOCUS ON FIXING YOUR FLAWS, 
LEARN TO LOVE THEM INSTEAD. 
When you bring love to your flaws and care for them with kindness you create a positive space around you where the true transformation you're looking for will eventually happen. 
Love is the ultimate antidote for all suffering and the most powerful force in the universe. Never forget that. ‚ú®
